<s> Mind you, I don't really like having such  </s>
<s> a wealth of punctuation inside names.  </s>
<s> I don't think the user of a language is helped a lot by having the choice between maple_syrup-count and maple-syrup.count and so on.  </s>
<s> I think it is liable to lead to more uncaught errors and more user confusion.  </s>
<s> It is just that XML does it.  </s>
<s> So we have to be compatible - but we don't have to encourage it.  </s>
<s> After all, one can always use the uri form.  </s>
<s> N3 uses punctuation for semantics.  </s>
<s> XML doesn't have to worry about it because it uses angle brackets around tag names.  </s>
<s> The "." is very common parlance for a path step, and allowing ?x.mother.age  </s>
<s> makes a lot of sense to OO types.  </s>
<s> I could imagine restricting it to ?x!mother!age but its looks weirder to the uninitiated.  </s>
